column1: OSF | Wave 10.0.2 | ACC3 | Getting error in OM for incorrect digit length for CustomerNumber
column32:
We are performing one negative scenario for error handling epic in which the order is failed &  OM will send cancellation document "5260_OSF_Email" to the customers informing them about the cancelled order but we are getting below error in OM for cancelled order 

*Error:* n/a-n/a-n/a-00000, ValidationRuleViolation, n/a, n/a, n/a, 16498396, 16498396, Solstice CustomerNumber must be of length 12 but the ID '000000000' is of length 9

*Test details :*
*Document id :16498396*

*Steps to Reproduce:* 
1) Login to telesales channel 
2) Place order during MINT downtime or some technical issue 
3) submit order 
4) wait for 24 retries 
5) Order should get cancelled as ULM ID is not created 
6) check email received 

*Actual Result :* Order is faling in OM with error & cancellation email not received to the customer 

{*}Expected Result :{*}Cancellation mail should be sent to customer on same email id
column188: Cancellation document will not be recieved to the customer
column737:
08/Oct/25 3:26 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Feedback:

We have performed our analysis and found the reported error in PR OM application logs.

Adapter ID : *16498396*

_11:46:28.473 ERROR c.t.o.e.t.DebugErrorHandlerAction - XML/Reporting data = source: OGW;client:MMC;commtype:mail;messageid:16498396;correlationid:16498396_

_11:46:28.474 ERROR c.t.o.e.t.DebugErrorHandlerAction - Solstice CustomerNumber must be of length 12 but the ID '000000000' is of length 9_

_com.trivadis.oms.common.exception.ValidationRuleViolation: Solstice CustomerNumber must be of length 12 but the ID '000000000' is of length 9_

Furthermore, it has been observed that all orders placed to date with the document type *‘5260_osf_EMail’* are currently reflecting an ERROR status within PRROMDB.

Thus, we have highlighted this issue to OM Development Team and currently, waiting for their input.

We will keep you informed as soon as we receive a response from their side.;;;
column738:
08/Oct/25 4:03 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Latest feedback:

“ the error is valid. It‘s related to incorrect length of the customernumber.

 

<ns2:Kundennummer>000000000</ns2:Kundennummer>

<ns2:KundennummerArt>SOLSTICE</ns2:KundennummerArt>

<ns2:Kundenklasse>OSFC</ns2:Kundenklasse

 

Specification:

Length of customernumber  =12 for KundennummerArt=SOLSTICE.

Length of customernumber  =9 for KundennummerArt=BAN.

 

There are 2 options to avoid this problem related to attached  input data

               update
 # KundennummerArt =BAN or
 # Kundennummer= extending up to 12 digits 000000000000  ”;;;
column740:
08/Oct/25 6:12 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;Hi [~pallavi.kokate1@vodafone.com] ,

As per the specification document and the attached example, the Kundennummer was defined as a 9-digit number.

Therefore, from OGW’s perspective, the implementation aligns with the intended design.

https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-60833;;;
column741:
09/Oct/25 12:22 AM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~affan.baragazi@vodafone.com]  we have to change it to 12 as its always 12 for FusionC , not sure what went wrong.

Please check email from Gerd and propose if we can fix it from OGW side and when;;;

we need to clear the entries from ogw_search_criteria table 

Before proceeding with the deletion of entries where omnius_order_id starts with '480', we’d like to highlight a few critical implications to ensure informed decision-making:
 # The ACC team should acknowledge and take ownership of any downstream issues that may arise due to the removal of older order data. These orders may still be referenced in legacy/active orders.
 # If the data for this orders still exists in related tables like jesi_wf_amdocs_subscribe or Cassandra, and the same sequence is reused later, it could trigger a unique constraint violation. ** Please ensure the data is cleaned up across all relevant tables before proceeding.

only after [~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  confirms above impact. [~affan.baragazi@vodafone.com] will handle the deletion. After that, we’ll monitor the functionality to ensure everything works as expected, will update further ;;;

column746:
16/Sep/25 5:22 PM;natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com;On VFP side nothing was changed!

This issue seems to be related to the PST bug: [[PSTBUG-3509] PAPI | OSF | VKD,VFW | All orders are failing with Delivery & Billing address error message - DE Jira|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PSTBUG-3509]

Answer from developer:

Hello,
The issue is in IBP (IRIS) when it contacts AdsFacade to validate the sent addresses. The exact field causing the issue is houseNumberAddition. When the field is omitted in the request, AdsFacade returns an asterisk in the candidate addresses. When the address is compared with the candidate address returned from AdsFacade, the validation fails (becasue null != '*'). 
A workaround can be applied in IRIS to ignore asterisks in both the address and the candidate address when comparing them as it's already a wildcard.

[~anna-mariya.robeto@vodafone.com] could you please update us as soon as the PST bug is solved. The PST bug was created only fr test1b, but we have this issue on all ACC environments. Thank you;;;

column1: OSF || ACC Environments || Wave 10 || ACC1 & ACC3 | User accounts are facing ACCESS BLOCKED Issue
column32:
Hello Team

We are writing to report a recurring issue observed in the OSF ACC1/2/3 environments. Recently, users have been experiencing *ACCESS BLOCKED* errors. Even after activating the user accounts and resetting their passwords, the issue persists.

To address this, we are raising a defect so that your team can investigate and troubleshoot the root cause. This issue has been occurring consistently over the past few months.

As a temporary workaround, we are creating alternate user accounts for the requestors to ensure their tasks are not impacted.

We kindly request your team to investigate this issue and share your findings along with a resolution plan

Below are examples user accounts details those are facing ACCESS BLOCKED issues:
[harish.madipeddi1@vodafone.com|mailto:harish.madipeddi1@vodafone.com]
[yogesh.borade1@vodafone.com|mailto:yogesh.borade1@vodafone.com]
ashutosh.chavan2

Find below snip as reference

column32:
While performing below scenario :
Perform ILS of solstice order with alternative delivery address --> Delivery to DHL Packstation
We have observed that <ContactRole>{*}LC{*}</ContactRole> is populated in the submit order fulfilment logs for delivery address --> Delivery to DHL Packstation
Order ID : 475247(ILS) ,475247

Steps to Reproduce :
1)Login to telesales channel
2)Select existing solstice customer
3)Change tariff
4)Select delivery option as "delivery to DHL packstation"

Expected Result :ContactRole attribute value should be *DC* upon selecting delivery address as "delivery to DHL packstation"
Actual Result : ContactRole = *LC* is populated instead of ContactRole = *DC* in the logs

hi [~daniel.loos@vodafone.com] [~pranjali.shetake@vodafone.com] 
 
For the mentioned Omnius Order Id: 473533, Submit Order logs is populated with correct date format 2025-07-15 as expected.

 For OIL to OGW logs -
<DeliveryDate>
<ns3:Value sourceSystem="ALL">20250715</ns3:Value>
</DeliveryDate>

SubmitOrder Logs URL:  ([https://dea766yw.eito-dublin.local/archive/I09/2025/7/1/Send/SOAPRequest/473553_73106054-3b09-48eb-8cb4-43d6c75067a3_Request_18bc7657-f198-4eca-84b8-71accdb4b99c.xml])

 OIL to OGW is sending as per interface specification. Same format is used for FixedNet/DSL and it was agreed during design that we have to use same format for FucsionC as well. We (OSE) do not provide json format , its OGW. This needs to be checked from OGW side.;;;

column755:
08/Jul/25 3:55 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;Hi [~pranjali.shetake@vodafone.com] ,

As per the SubmitOrder request received from Omnius, we are getting the deliveryDate as below:

                       <DeliveryDate>
                            <ns3:Value {*}sourceSystem="ALL"{*}>20250715</ns3:Value>
                        </DeliveryDate>

In OGW xsd for SubmitOrder this field is defined as an array, hence we are forwarding the same while converting it into JSON request please refer below snippet from xsd:
            <xsd:element name="DeliveryDate" nillable="true" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
                <xsd:complexType>
                    <xsd:sequence>
                        <xsd:element ref="vfdecommon:Value" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="{*}unbounded{*}"/>
                    </xsd:sequence>
                </xsd:complexType>
            </xsd:element>
The implementation of *DeliveryDate* is similar to that of *DealerCode* which is in the request and accepted by SOI.;;;
column756: 08/Jul/25 3:55 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;This is as per the implemented design for OGW.;;;
